= Dragon Warrior IV (NES) - SRAM Map =

This page documents the battery-backed save RAM layout for Dragon Warrior IV.

'''Data Status:''' Party member structure verified. Some addresses remain unverified (marked with ???).

== Overview ==

Dragon Warrior IV uses the MMC5 mapper which provides 8KB of battery-backed SRAM at CPU addresses $6000-$7fff. This is mirrored in the save file as addresses $0000-$1fff. The save structure allocates fixed blocks for each of the eight playable characters, followed by global game state variables.

=== Key Features ===

* '''8KB total SRAM''' - Standard MMC5 save size
* '''8 character slots''' - 30 bytes each at fixed offsets
* '''24-bit gold/EXP''' - Supports values up to 16,777,215
* '''Chapter tracking''' - Saves current chapter (0-4)
* '''Tactics setting''' - AI behavior persisted across saves

