== Character Data Structure ==

Each character occupies 30 bytes ($1e) in SRAM. The structure is identical for all 8 playable characters.

{| class="wikitable"
! Offset !! Size !! Description
|-
| $00 || 1 || Status flags (bit 5=Poison, 6=Paralyzed, 7=Alive)
|-
| $01-$02 || 2 || Current HP (little-endian word)
|-
| $03-$04 || 2 || Current MP
|-
| $05 || 1 || Level (1-99)
|-
| $06-$0a || 5 || Stats: Str, Agi, Vit, Int, Luck
|-
| $0b || 1 || Unknown
|-
| $0c-$0d || 2 || Max HP
|-
| $0e-$0f || 2 || Max MP
|-
| $10-$12 || 3 || Experience (24-bit, little-endian)
|-
| $13-$1a || 8 || Item slots (8 bytes)
|-
| $1b-$1c || 2 || Battle spell flags
|-
| $1d || 1 || Overworld spell flags
|}

